This paper examines the negativity and positivity of word usage in posts by common users of two popular online social networks, Instagram and Ask.fm, that are often used for cyberbullying. This analysis falls under the categories of social media analysis (cs.SI), cyberbullying (cs.CY), social networks (cs.SOC), natural language processing (cs.CL), and security and privacy (cs.CR).
